The formula for the probability of the union of two events A and B is given by $P(A \cup B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A \cap B)$, where $P(A \cap B)$ is the probability of the intersection of A and B.

## Step 3: Apply the formula to find $P(A \cap B)$
